@startuml
title POST /api/v1/registration/code-validations (200 OK)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "validate_registration\n_code_view" as View
participant "AnonAuthThrottle" as Throttle
participant "RegistrationCode\nValidateInputSerializer" as Serializer
participant "validate_registration\n_code()" as Service
database Postgres

Client -> View: POST /registration/code-validations\n{code: "REG-abc123..."}
View -> Throttle: check rate limit
Throttle --> View: OK (AllowAny)
View -> Serializer: is_valid(data)
Serializer --> View: validated {code}

View -> Service: validate_registration_code(code)
Service -> Service: _registration_code_hashes_for_lookup(code)\nHMAC hash with SECRET_KEY + fallbacks
Service -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ?
Postgres --> Service: RegistrationCode row
Service -> Service: check archived_at is None
Service -> Service: check is_active == True
Service -> Service: check expires_at > now
Service -> Service: check times_used < max_uses
Service --> View: RegistrationCode (valid)

View --> Client: 200 OK\n{valid: true, code_type: "STUDENT",\ncontext: {course_name, teacher_name}}
@enduml
